Johannesburg - Sixteen people were injured, one critically, when a taxi they were travelling in collided with a light-delivery van on the R55 in Kyalami, north of Johannesburg, ER24 said on Friday. ER24 Spokeperson, Russel Meiring, said when rescue services arrived at the scene, they found the taxi in the middle of the intersection. Both the taxi and the delivery were badly damaged. “Several occupants from the taxi were found walking around on the scene and on assessment paramedics found that approximately 16 people had been injured in the collision and one critically,” Meiring said. Meiring said paramedics treated the patients and provided the critically injured one with advanced life support interventions before airlifting the patient by a private medical helicopter to a nearby hospital for further treatment. The remaining patients were taken to hospitals in the area for treatment. African News Agency